    <etym xml:lang="ru">Прош. причастик от глагола *%icajyn%i, снабженное суффиксом %iæg%i
        (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). Глагол
        *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>čyā-</w><gloss><q>покоиться</q></gloss></mentioned> сохранился только в
        сращении с превербом %iæn%i-: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> : <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æncad"/> ‘покоиться’. Такую же морфологическую структуру, как %icadæg%i
        (прош. причастие + %iæg%i), имеют <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘чистый’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘мелкий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/>
        ‘живой’ и др. У поэта <bibl><author>Коста</author></bibl> (в черновых рукописях) встречается
        также форма %iæncadæg%i. Взятое без суффикса -%iæg%i осетинское <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                ><lang/><w>cad-</w></mentioned> точно соответствует <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>šād</w><gloss><q>радостный</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. См. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref
                target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Past participle form of the verb %icajyn%i with the suffix %iæg%i
        (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). The verb
        *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>čyā-</w><gloss><q>repose</q></gloss></mentioned> remained only bound with the
        preverb %iæn%i-: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> : <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æncad"/> ‘repose’. The same morphological structure, as %icadæg%i (past
        participle + %iæg%i), is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘pure’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘small’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/>
        ‘alive’ etc. The poet <bibl><author>Kosta</author></bibl> had (in drafts) the form
        %iæncadæg%i. The Ossetic word <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>cad-</w></mentioned>
        without suffix -%iæg%i exactly corresponds <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>šād</w><gloss><q>happy</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. See <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref
                target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
